  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rural Water Supply and Sanitation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) Access to safe drinking water for 18,090 people in 9 villages in Khagarijan region by December 2013. Constructing 25 wells in the 9 villages.

2) Latrine facilities provided to 140 families by the end of December 2013.

3) Educate and sensitize 18,090 people on proper health, hygiene and sanitation practices by the end of July 2014 through extensive outreach. Reducing incidence of waterborne disease.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To provide access to clean water and sanitation facilities and education about proper hygiene practices to the poor and marginalized in the deprived Assam state.</narrative>
